  "prompt": "What do travel sites like Expedia, Kayak, Travelocity, and Priceline charge for a booking transaction?",
  "response": "These online travel agencies (OTAs) generally charge fees that vary depending on the type of booking:\n\n1. Flights: Most OTAs do not charge an explicit booking fee, but they earn money through commissions from airlines (typically 5-10% of the ticket price).\n\n2. Hotels: Similar to flights, they earn commissions from hotels (usually around 10-25% of the room rate).\n\n3. Car rentals: Commissions range from 5-10% of the rental price.\n\n4. Vacation packages: They may earn bundled commissions from multiple services.\n\nSome sites might charge a small service fee ($5-$10) for certain bookings, but this varies. Always check the specific terms and total price before booking.",
